    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-22T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-22T01:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12317: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-22T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 22, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1194. The informant known to the Department informed me this morning that the
                    German, Finnish and Rumanian armies are attacking the Soviet Union along the
                    entire front and that Sevastopol has been bombed this morning.<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d156fn89">See also telegram No. 1197, June 22, from the Ambassador
                        in the Soviet Union, <ref target="#pg_625">p. 625</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I shall appreciate any action the Department may be able to take to stop the flow
                    of visa and other routine telegrams to this office as they are likely to
                    interfere with the receipt of telegrams of greater importance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
